                <catalogueItem>
                    <num>162</num>
                    <title>Caligula's palace and bridge</title>
                    <note>
                        <quote>"<l>What now remains of all the mighty bridge</l>
                            <l>Which made the Lucrine lake an inner pool,</l>
                            <l>Caligula, but massy fragments left,</l>
                            <l>As monuments of doubt and ruined hopes</l>
                            <l>Yet gleaming in the morning's ray, that tell</l>
                            <l>How Baia's shore was loved in times fone by ?</l>" MS. Fallacies of
                            Hope.</quote>
                    </note>
                </catalogueItem>
                <catalogueDesc>
                    <person>
                        <persName>
                            <forename>J. M. W.</forename>
